<h3>Mountain Biking</h3>

<p>Winter Park &amp; Grand County boasts some of the best mountain biking opportunities anywhere in Colorado. From heart-pounding high altitude climbs to fairly level trails winding along the valley floor, there is something here for everyone. 600 miles of marked, mapped and user-friendly trails wind through the fields of wild flowers, over the tops of the mountain peaks and back into the forest. Winter Park Resort has over 50 miles of lift accessible varied terrain trails and 3 terrain parks. Take your bike on specially equipped Zephyr Chairlift to the top, chose a route (color-coded by the level of difficulty) and bomb down the mountain or find a trail that will hook up with the other 600 miles of rails in the area. Enjoy the ride!</p>

<p>Pick up a free copy of The Official Mountain Bike &amp; Trail Guide to Winter Park and The Fraser Valley at the Chamber of Commerce.</p>

<h3>Fishing</h3>

<p>There are many fishing options in Grand County and the nearby area. With 1,000 miles of streams, 1,000 acres of high mountain lakes and 11,000 acres of reservoirs, a fishing trip to this particular area of Colorado will reward anglers of all levels of expertise. Trout and salmon are the most sought after prizes in mountain fishing and all through Grand County, lurking below the water&rsquo;s surface you will find Mackinaw and Kokanee salmon as well as rainbow, brook, German brown and cutthroat trout.</p>

<p>Grand County streams enticed President Eisenhower here in the 1940&rsquo;s and 50&rsquo;s. Grey Reef was #1 on the American Angler list of the 25 best places to go for big fish. Whether young or old, on private waters or public, fishing by wading or by boat, the waters of Grand County have something for everyone.</p>

<p>We highly recommend Jeff Ehlert, Guide &amp; Owner of Grand County Fishing Company. Give him a call at <a href="tel:970-726-5231">(970)-726-5231</a> or visit his <a href="http://www.grandflyfishing.com" target="_blank">website</a>.</p>

<p>Need a fishing license, poles, rods, reels or just some local information? The experienced guides at Grand County Fishing can help you make the most of your time on the water. From insider knowledge to equipment, rentals and supplies for anglers of all ages and abilities, Grand County Fishing Company is ready to help. Visit Jeff and his staff at his shop in Fraser, Colorado. Located on Hwy 40 in the Alco Shopping Center in Fraser, just across from the Safeway Grocery Store.</p>

<p>Jeff offers wade and float trips, public and private water, full and half day trips. He can custom tailor a guided trip for you. Call <a href="tel:970-531-9998">(970)-531-9998</a> to book your Guided trip now. Whatever the season, Grand County Fishing Company can take you to the best fishing spots. <a href="http://www.grandflyfishing.com" target="_blank">Click the link</a> for Grand County Fly Fishing Tips.</p>

<h3><a href="http://www.grandadventureballoon.com/home.html" target="_blank">Grand Adventure Hot Air Balloon Tours</a></h3>

<p>A wonderful way to see the Rockies. A one hour tour followed by a champagne breakfast. Local tip: Always ask for the first available flight. Flights may be canceled due to bad weather or high winds aloft. Call Grand Adventure Balloon Tours before leaving for the lift off location. For reservations and information call <a href="tel:970-887-1340">(970) 887-1340</a> or <a href="http://www.grandadventureballoon.com/home.html" target="_blank">visit their website</a>.</p>

<h3>White Water Rafting</h3>

<p>Enjoy an action packed ride thrilling ride in Colorado&rsquo;s white water or take a leisurely float trip. Either way, it&rsquo;s sure to be a good time.</p>

<p>Half-day, full day and overnight trips are available. Check with the rafting company for details and rates.</p>

