<h3>Golfing</h3>

<p>Destination Golf at 8,000 feet! Watch your ball fly 15% farther framed by spectacular mountain views. Choose from four outstanding, distinctively different golf courses in and around Winter Park and Grand County.</p>

<h4>Pole Creek Golf Club</h4>

<p>Pole Creek Golf Club is a tree-lined, links-style 27-hole course rated by Golf Digest in 1998 as the &lsquo;Best New Course in America&rdquo; and &ldquo;Number One Place to Play in Colorado&rdquo;. Three distinct 9-hole courses (The Ranch, The Meadow, and The Ridge) incorporate native lodgepole pines, valley meadows, sagebrush and a variety of water hazards. Pro golfer JT Thompson calls the Ridge &ldquo;the most spectacular View in Colorado&rdquo;. Call <a href="tel:1-800-511-5076">1-800-511-5076</a> for tee-times.</p>

<h4>Grand Lake Golf Course</h4>

<p>Known as the &ldquo;Crown Jewel of Mountain Courses&rdquo; this 18-hole mountain course is adjacent to Rocky Mountain National Park. Set amidst a pristine mountain setting, the challenging fairways offer dramatic views of the surrounding snow-capped peaks of the Never Summer Range and Grand Lake and glimpses of wildlife sharing the tees. Call <a href="tel:970-627-8008">970-627-8008</a>.</p>

<h4>Headwaters Golf Course at Granby Ranch</h4>

<p>An open style 18-hole links style course tucked between the waters of the Fraser River and the majestic Rocky mountains. Natural obstacles including wetlands, lakes, trees and large deep bunkers o er golfers of every ability an exceptional experience. Call <a href="tel:888-283-7458">888-283-7458</a>.</p>

<h4>Grand Elk Ranch &amp; Club</h4>

<p>The newest addition to Grand County’s mountain golf paradise. Grand Elk is Colorado’s first Heathland-style golf course. Featuring gently rolling fairways and strategically placed hazards this course offers five sets of tee boxes and views of protected wetlands that are habitat for hundreds of birds. Call <a href="tel:866-272-9822">866-272-9822</a>.</p>

